                <head>307. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The Foreign Ministers did not meet on Saturday May 16 or Sunday May 17. Secretary
                    of State <persName corresp="#p_HCA1">Herter</persName> took advantage of this
                    hiatus to fly to Rome on May 16 for conversations with Prime Minister <persName
                        corresp="#p_SA1">Segni</persName> and Foreign Minister <persName
                        corresp="#p_PG1">Pella</persName>. During the course of a meeting at the
                    Villa Madama from 1:30 to 4:30 p.m., <persName corresp="#p_HCA1"
                        >Herter</persName> briefed the Italian leaders on the first week of the
                    Foreign Ministers Conference and explained the Western Peace Plan in some
                    detail. A memorandum of this conversation, US/<gloss target="#t_MC1"
                    >MC</gloss>/24, is in Department of State, Conference Files: Lot 64 D 560,
                        <gloss target="#t_CF1">CF</gloss> 1350.</p>
            </div>
